RIFT VALLEY FEVER - EASTERN AFRICA (06): KENYA
**********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Sun 21 Jan 2007
From: S K Sharif <sksharif@africaonline.co.ke>
Source: Ministry of Health, Kenya

Rift Valley fever update, Kenya
-------------------------------
The outbreak of Rift Valley fever in Kenya that started in December 2006 in
Garissa District in North Eastern Kenya has claimed 111 lives as of 20 Jan
2007. The outbreak started in Garissa District, and cases have been
reported from other districts in North Eastern Province, Coast Province,
and Eastern Province. The breakdown of cases is as follows:
North Eastern Province
----------------------
Garissa District: cases 161, deaths 56
Ijara District: cases 118, deaths 22
Wajir District: cases 27, deaths 12
Coast Province
--------------
Tana River District: cases 16, deaths 7
Kilifi District: cases 30, deaths 11
Malindi District: cases 7, deaths 2
Taita Taveta: cases 1, deaths 1
Eastern Province
----------------
Isiolo District: cases 7, deaths 0
Total cases as of 20 Jan 2007 are 367 cases with 111 deaths (case fatality
rate 30 per cent). The cases reported from Ijara are not new cases but
cases which were not reported to the Province and thus missed in the
initial reports. The Vet Department has also confirmed positive cases in
livestock from Maragua District in Central Province.
--
Dr S K Sharif OGW, MBChB, MMed, DLSHTM, MSc
Chief Medical Specialist
Ministry of Health
Kenya
<sksharif@africaonline.co.ke>
[ProMED-mail thanks Dr Sharif for provision of this update. A map of the
Administrative Districts of Kenya can be viewed at
<http://ag.arizona.edu/OALS/ALN/aln57/bruins2.html>. - Mod.CP]
